  "prompt": "What exactly is 'pins and needles?",
  "response": "\"Pins and needles\" is a common term used to describe a sensation of tingling, prickling, or a feeling of numbness in various parts of the body, often in the arms, legs, fingers, or toes. This sensation is medically referred to as \"paresthesia.\" \n\nThe feeling typically occurs when pressure is applied to a nerve, often due to staying in one position for too long, which restricts blood flow or puts pressure on the nerve. When the pressure is relieved and circulation returns, the tingling sensation usually subsides. \n\nIn some cases, pins and needles can also result from other causes, such as nerve irritation, carpal tunnel syndrome, multiple sclerosis, or peripheral neuropathy. If the sensation is persistent or accompanied by other symptoms, it's advisable to consult a healthcare professional for a thorough evaluation.",
